# npm registry (personal project)

This repo is under **`~/hobby-projects/agentic-swe`**. npm commands must target the **public** registry.

## Default

The repository includes **[`.npmrc`](../../.npmrc)** with:

```ini
registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
```

So `npm install`, `npm publish`, `npm whoami`, etc. already resolve to the public registry when run from this directory.

## When running npm in chat or scripts

- Prefer running commands **from the repo root** so `.npmrc` applies.
- If a command must be spelled out explicitly (e.g. docs, CI snippets), include:

  **`--registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/`**

  Examples:

  ```bash
  npm publish --registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
  npm whoami --registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
  npm view agentic-swe version --registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
  ```

- **Do not** assume the user’s global npm is pointed at the public registry (work machines may override).

## Optional user check

```bash
npm config get registry
```

Should show `https://registry.npmjs.org/` when using this repo’s `.npmrc`.
